Setting Up RabbitMQ Locally Using Docker

Install Docker on my machine, and make sure it is running.

pull the RabbitMQ image with the management plugin and runs it in a Docker container by using this command:
docker run -d --hostname rabbitmq-server --name rabbitmq -p 5672:5672 -p 15672:15672 rabbitmq:3-management

Access RabbitMQ Management Dashboard:

URL: http://localhost:15672
Username: guest
Password: guest
